<AbstractNarration>&lt;br/&gt;The proposer has constructed a Grothendieck topology for varieties over finite fields &lt;br/&gt;such that, modulo standard conjectures, special values of zeta-functions can be &lt;br/&gt;computed as Euler characteristics (in a suitable sense) of certain motivic sheaves or &lt;br/&gt;complexes of sheaves.  He now intends to work on the construction of a similar &lt;br/&gt;Grothendieck topology for schemes over number rings. &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;The Riemann zeta-function (discovered by Riemann in the nineteenth century) and its &lt;br/&gt;generalizations express many deep relations between analysis and number theory.  &lt;br/&gt;These relations should be consequences of a deep underlying topological structure.  &lt;br/&gt;This project is an investigation into the properties which that structure would have to possess.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
